kel resurrects McWorter’s great achievement of self-determinism, independence, and the will to exist. Shackel describes a cooperative effort by two universities, the state museum, the New Philadelphia Association, and numerous descendents to explore the history and archaeology of this unusual multi-racial community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCommunity lifezIllinoiszNew PhiladelphiaxHistory. 0aCultural pluralismzIllinoiszNew PhiladelphiaxHistory. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zIllinoiszNew Philadelphia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026630840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094783240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947832423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947832/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY